public class codeforces_579_A {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner str = new Scanner(System.in);
        int n = str.nextInt();
        String s = "";
        while (n > 0) {
            int x = n % 2;
            n /= 2;
            s += x + "";
        }
        int ans = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '1') {
                ans++;
            }
        }
        System.out.println(ans);
    }
} Wait, the loop is while n>0, so the digits are collected in reverse order. For example, n=5 (101 in binary), the loop runs:

n=5: x=1, n becomes 2. s is "1"

n=2: x=0, n becomes 1. s is "10"

n=1: x=1, n becomes 0. s is "101" So the string is "101", which is correct.
